1
00:00:08,625 --> 00:00:09,416
[MAOU] What's this?

2
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:11,125
Vegetables, Sire.

3
00:00:11,208 --> 00:00:14,166
I suppose this is her
way of saying thank you.

4
00:00:14,250 --> 00:00:16,708
Allow me to ascertain
their safety for you.

5
00:00:21,333 --> 00:00:22,083
Is it good?

6
00:00:22,166 --> 00:00:24,875
Yes, Sire.
It's quite good.

7
00:00:26,083 --> 00:00:29,375
[ASHIYA] That's unusual, why
is there a key on the floor?

8
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,250
[MAOU] I'm guessing she opened
the window on her way out,

9
00:00:32,333 --> 00:00:34,083
and locked the door
from the outside,

10
00:00:34,166 --> 00:00:36,125
then tossed the key back in.

11
00:00:36,208 --> 00:00:39,916
Typical hero.
All exemplary in her conduct.

12
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:41,833
What would you have
done if you were her?

13
00:00:41,916 --> 00:00:43,291
[ASHIYA] Isn't it obvious?

14
00:00:43,375 --> 00:00:45,416
First, I would've
locked the door,

15
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:47,625
and then I would've
taken the key with me.

16
00:00:47,708 --> 00:00:49,000
[MAOU] Typical Demon.

17
00:00:49,083 --> 00:00:51,041
[ASHIYA] Would you have
me any other way, Sire?

18
00:02:32,416 --> 00:02:35,083
[EMI] I feel so violated.

19
00:02:39,791 --> 00:02:42,166
[MALE NEWSCASTER 3A] In other
news, multiple shots were fired

20
00:02:42,250 --> 00:02:45,083
in the Shibuya area
before dawn this morning.

21
00:02:45,166 --> 00:02:47,916
The area was littered
with numerous bullet holes.

22
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,416
An abandoned bicycle,

23
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:51,833
hit multiple times, was found
at the scene of the crime.

24
00:02:51,916 --> 00:02:53,750
[EMI] Oh, unbelievable!

25
00:02:53,833 --> 00:02:55,250
Those jerk wads.

26
00:02:55,333 --> 00:02:57,541
Well, guess it's not my problem.

27
00:02:58,291 --> 00:02:59,708
[MALE NEWSCASTER 3A]
Police are also investigating

28
00:02:59,791 --> 00:03:02,250
possible links between this
incident and a recent string

29
00:03:02,333 --> 00:03:04,708
of late-night muggings
and storefront robberies.

30
00:03:04,791 --> 00:03:07,333
Although the exact nature of
the connection remains unclear.

31
00:03:07,416 --> 00:03:09,625
[CHIHO'S MOTHER] That's a hop,
skip, and a jump from here.

32
00:03:09,708 --> 00:03:12,375
Darling, isn't that really
close to where you work?

33
00:03:17,916 --> 00:03:19,833
[CHIHO] I'm not joking
or imagining things!

34
00:03:19,916 --> 00:03:22,125
I really think an
earthquake is coming!

35
00:03:22,208 --> 00:03:24,541
So, if you don't mind,

36
00:03:24,625 --> 00:03:27,375
could I ask your advice
about this in person?

37
00:03:30,375 --> 00:03:31,750
[CHIHO] And "Send!"

38
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:35,958
[MAOU] Okay. Does
tomorrow evening work?

39
00:03:36,041 --> 00:03:37,666
I've got the day off.

40
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:40,041
And you're not on
shift either, are you?

41
00:03:42,500 --> 00:03:44,375
[CHIHO'S MOTHER] Chiho,
are you working today?

42
00:03:44,458 --> 00:03:46,875
Uh. No. I'm not.

43
00:03:46,958 --> 00:03:51,166
But I am real busy today--you
know, with lots of other stuff.

44
00:03:51,250 --> 00:03:52,958
[CHIHO'S MOTHER]
You just be safe out there.

45
00:03:53,041 --> 00:03:55,083
Why wouldn't
I be? Safe, heh.

46
00:03:55,166 --> 00:03:56,333
That's my middle name!

47
00:03:56,416 --> 00:03:56,958
[CHIHO'S MOTHER]
This neighborhood's not like

48
00:03:57,041 --> 00:03:58,333
it used to be.

49
00:03:58,416 --> 00:03:59,833
Yeah. I know, Mom.

50
00:03:59,916 --> 00:04:01,583
[CHIHO'S MOTHER]
What is the matter with you?

51
00:04:01,666 --> 00:04:04,000
Um. Nothing, I'm fine.

52
00:04:04,083 --> 00:04:05,333
[CHIHO'S MOTHER] Chiho!

53
00:04:05,416 --> 00:04:07,458
[RIKA] Emi. You heard
about the shooting, yeah?

54
00:04:07,541 --> 00:04:09,458
Wasn't that pretty close
to where you live?

55
00:04:09,541 --> 00:04:12,166
No, I'm like three
stops from there.

56
00:04:12,250 --> 00:04:13,416
[RIKA] That's crazy.

57
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:15,041
Anyway, whatcha doin' for lunch?

58
00:04:15,125 --> 00:04:17,208
Wanna hit that curry place
I told you about?

59
00:04:17,291 --> 00:04:19,583
Yes, there'll be a line but
it is totes worth the wait.

60
00:04:19,666 --> 00:04:23,791
Uhh.. Thanks, but I'm way too
busy to stand in line today.

61
00:04:23,875 --> 00:04:25,125
Plus, I lost my wallet.

62
00:04:25,208 --> 00:04:26,833
What? That sucks!

63
00:04:26,916 --> 00:04:27,875
[EMI] Yeah, and
now I have to fill out

64
00:04:27,958 --> 00:04:30,208
a bunch of forms on my break.

65
00:04:32,666 --> 00:04:34,916
Thank you
for your call today.

66
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:37,250
I'm Emi Yusa,
how can I help you?

67
00:04:37,333 --> 00:04:38,416
[MALE YOUTH] "Yusa"?

68
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:39,875
Sounds to me like you're fitting

69
00:04:39,958 --> 00:04:43,000
in quite nicely,
Emilia the Hero.

70
00:04:43,083 --> 00:04:45,166
[EMI] May I ask who is calling?

71
00:04:45,250 --> 00:04:48,375
[MALE YOUTH] Someone who knows
'bout "the Hero and the Devil."

72
00:04:48,458 --> 00:04:49,875
And that's not all.

73
00:04:49,958 --> 00:04:52,916
I'm gonna do everything in my
power to destroy you both.

74
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,375
[EMI] Understood, sir.

75
00:04:54,458 --> 00:04:57,250
I'll do whatever it takes to
keep that from happening.

76
00:04:57,333 --> 00:04:58,416
[MALE YOUTH] I gotta admit,

77
00:04:58,500 --> 00:05:00,791
I didn't expect you
two to join forces.

78
00:05:00,875 --> 00:05:04,000
[EMI] That was not our
company's desired result either.

79
00:05:04,083 --> 00:05:05,958
[MALE YOUTH] I guess not.

80
00:05:06,041 --> 00:05:09,666
Either way, King Satan
will be taken out.

81
00:05:09,750 --> 00:05:11,875
As will Emilia the Hero.

82
00:05:11,958 --> 00:05:13,708
It's Ente Isla's will.

83
00:05:13,791 --> 00:05:15,875
[EMI] Is that right?

84
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:20,000
I'm afraid we won't
have any specifics

85
00:05:20,083 --> 00:05:22,791
'til we've had a chance to
investigate the situation.

86
00:05:22,875 --> 00:05:24,541
[MALE YOUTH] The Devil
and the Hero running away

87
00:05:24,625 --> 00:05:27,875
from a little gunfire?
That "situation"?

88
00:05:27,958 --> 00:05:30,666
And how're you
gonna investigate?

89
00:05:31,208 --> 00:05:32,166
[EMI thinking] A vile tone
that seems to echo

90
00:05:32,250 --> 00:05:34,583
from the pits of darkness.

91
00:05:34,666 --> 00:05:36,333
He's a Demon.

92
00:05:37,166 --> 00:05:39,041
[EMI] Alciel is the
only reputable general

93
00:05:39,125 --> 00:05:40,875
still walking among us.

94
00:05:40,958 --> 00:05:44,333
So that would make you nothing.

95
00:05:44,416 --> 00:05:45,708
If you think
you can scare me

96
00:05:45,791 --> 00:05:48,750
with words like "Ente Isla's
will" you're dead wrong.

97
00:05:48,833 --> 00:05:52,291
I don't listen to idle threats
from nobodies like you.

98
00:05:52,375 --> 00:05:54,333
[MALE YOUTH] When this
is all said and done...

99
00:05:54,416 --> 00:05:57,791
I guarantee you'll be
singing a different tune.

100
00:06:04,875 --> 00:06:06,958
[EMI] Takes all kinds, huh?

101
00:06:08,041 --> 00:06:09,958
[EMI] Hey, so how
'bout that curry place.

102
00:06:10,041 --> 00:06:13,208
I remembered how busy
the bank is during lunch.

103
00:06:15,458 --> 00:06:16,875
Yeah, hello?

104
00:06:16,958 --> 00:06:18,208
[MALE COP 3A] Hello there.

105
00:06:18,291 --> 00:06:20,875
I'm trying to get in touch
with a Miss Emi Yusa?

106
00:06:20,958 --> 00:06:23,250
[EMI] Yes. That's me.

107
00:06:23,333 --> 00:06:26,208
[MALE COP 3A] I'm calling
from the Yoyogi Police Station.

108
00:06:26,291 --> 00:06:28,916
[EMI] Huh? The police?

109
00:06:36,416 --> 00:06:37,833
[MAOU] Didn't think there
was a snowball's chance

110
00:06:37,916 --> 00:06:39,833
at home they'd ID
us from that bike.

111
00:06:39,916 --> 00:06:41,208
These cops are good.

112
00:06:41,291 --> 00:06:42,583
Well, we were
definitely right

113
00:06:42,666 --> 00:06:43,916
about one thing.

114
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:46,291
Regarding her age,
the Hero "fudged the truth."

115
00:06:46,375 --> 00:06:47,791
If I remember correctly,

116
00:06:47,875 --> 00:06:49,708
she's only about
seventeen or eighteen.

117
00:06:49,791 --> 00:06:51,166
Yeah, I told you that.

118
00:06:51,250 --> 00:06:53,625
But she must've registered
as being at least twenty;

119
00:06:53,708 --> 00:06:55,166
no idea why though.

120
00:06:55,250 --> 00:06:58,041
I thought women lied about
their age to appear younger.

121
00:06:58,125 --> 00:07:00,833
I don't understand
why "fudge" means "lie."

122
00:07:01,375 --> 00:07:03,958
[EMI] Who the
crap cares about that?

123
00:07:04,041 --> 00:07:05,250
Why me?

124
00:07:05,333 --> 00:07:08,375
I wanna know, 'cause
I'm a little confused.

125
00:07:08,458 --> 00:07:09,708
I'm a Hero!

126
00:07:09,791 --> 00:07:11,625
So please tell me why
I just had to post bail

127
00:07:11,708 --> 00:07:14,708
for a couple asinine
good for nothing demons?

128
00:07:15,666 --> 00:07:17,583
Dude. Wouldja
please calm down?

129
00:07:17,666 --> 00:07:20,125
I'm sorry but we couldn't
think of anybody else.

130
00:07:20,208 --> 00:07:21,583
We weren't
positively overjoyed

131
00:07:21,666 --> 00:07:23,166
about asking for
your help either,

132
00:07:23,250 --> 00:07:24,208
but we had no choice.

133
00:07:24,291 --> 00:07:26,000
Well I for one never
thought I'd have

134
00:07:26,083 --> 00:07:27,541
to use my seal and ID card

135
00:07:27,625 --> 00:07:29,375
for something
that's just so dumb!

136
00:07:29,458 --> 00:07:30,541
I suppose I could've asked

137
00:07:30,625 --> 00:07:32,708
my manager at work
to help us out first.

138
00:07:32,791 --> 00:07:34,875
We can't annoy your
boss with such trifles.

139
00:07:34,958 --> 00:07:36,541
[EMI] So you annoy me, instead?

140
00:07:36,625 --> 00:07:37,833
Well, duh, causing trouble

141
00:07:37,916 --> 00:07:41,375
for heroes is the whole
point of being a devil.

142
00:07:41,458 --> 00:07:43,583
You win. Can't argue
with that logic.

143
00:07:43,666 --> 00:07:46,083
Don't be mad; we let
you stay at our place.

144
00:07:47,375 --> 00:07:49,000
Emi, relax, heroes
aren't supposed

145
00:07:49,083 --> 00:07:50,500
to have nervous breakdowns.

146
00:07:50,583 --> 00:07:51,666
Yeah?

147
00:07:51,750 --> 00:07:53,833
That's 'cause they
never met you! Jerks!

148
00:07:53,916 --> 00:07:55,458
Your fridge was
completely empty.

149
00:07:55,541 --> 00:07:58,250
Put a little more thought into
your grocery list next time!

150
00:07:58,333 --> 00:08:01,250
You're a Demon General and you
don't even know how to shop!

151
00:08:01,333 --> 00:08:02,583
[ASHIYA] I'm on a diet.

152
00:08:02,666 --> 00:08:06,291
I'm watching my calories.

153
00:08:06,375 --> 00:08:07,500
[EMI] Just so you know,

154
00:08:07,583 --> 00:08:08,958
I got a threatening
phone call at work today

155
00:08:09,041 --> 00:08:10,708
and it wasn't very pleasant.

156
00:08:10,791 --> 00:08:14,333
They're after you, too, Maou.
Mister King Satan himself.

157
00:08:14,416 --> 00:08:15,625
Thanks for the heads-up.

158
00:08:15,708 --> 00:08:17,083
It was just a heads-up.

159
00:08:17,166 --> 00:08:18,666
So don't get the wrong idea,

160
00:08:18,750 --> 00:08:20,708
I'm still going to be
the one to take you down.

161
00:08:20,791 --> 00:08:22,583
And don't you forget it!

162
00:08:22,666 --> 00:08:23,833
Just a reminder:

163
00:08:23,916 --> 00:08:26,541
we're in public so stop
acting like a psycho.

164
00:08:28,166 --> 00:08:29,625
You suck.

165
00:08:29,708 --> 00:08:31,333
Just make sure you don't get
murdered by some loser nobody

166
00:08:31,416 --> 00:08:33,916
before I get the
chance to kill you first!

167
00:08:37,625 --> 00:08:39,750
[MAOU] They're after
both of us, huh?

168
00:08:39,833 --> 00:08:42,791
And they called her
at work of all things.

169
00:08:43,708 --> 00:08:45,125
[ASHIYA] It's a diet
and workout plan...

170
00:08:45,208 --> 00:08:47,458
Oh, get a grip! Really!

171
00:08:47,541 --> 00:08:50,500
Nobody cares about your
stupid exercise routine!

172
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,791
[CHIHO] I'm home!

173
00:09:06,333 --> 00:09:09,416
[ASHIYA] To clarify: What time
are you meeting Miss Sasaki,

174
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:12,041
where are you meeting her,
and when can I expect you back?

175
00:09:12,125 --> 00:09:13,583
[MAOU] What are you, my mom now?

176
00:09:13,666 --> 00:09:16,041
Five o'clock, Shinjuku station.

177
00:09:16,416 --> 00:09:19,375
We do have a bit of
time to spare then.

178
00:09:19,458 --> 00:09:21,375
In that case,
Sire, you and I must go.

179
00:09:21,458 --> 00:09:23,125
Wait. Go where?

180
00:09:30,083 --> 00:09:32,375
[ASHIYA] Oh yes. Quite fabulous.

181
00:09:32,458 --> 00:09:33,583
Whatever, where
did you get the money

182
00:09:33,666 --> 00:09:35,791
to pay for this stuff anyway?

183
00:09:35,875 --> 00:09:37,791
Naturally I've set aside
a secret stash of savings

184
00:09:37,875 --> 00:09:39,833
for just this sort of emergency.

185
00:09:39,916 --> 00:09:41,333
[MAOU] "Emergency"?

186
00:09:41,416 --> 00:09:43,000
I'm just gonna sit
there, hear her out,

187
00:09:43,083 --> 00:09:45,875
and come home; I don't
think this is necessary.

188
00:09:45,958 --> 00:09:48,375
Au contraire, Sire!
Do you not see?

189
00:09:48,458 --> 00:09:50,875
A fragile teenage girl never
divulges her deepest fears

190
00:09:50,958 --> 00:09:53,125
to anyone but her
closest confidants!

191
00:09:53,208 --> 00:09:54,416
And that's you!

192
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:56,583
Did she or did she
not reveal it to you?

193
00:09:56,666 --> 00:09:59,541
Surely you cannot be blind to
what such a disclosure means?

194
00:09:59,625 --> 00:10:01,791
Yeah. Okay,
will ya just chill out?

195
00:10:01,875 --> 00:10:03,958
N'besides.

196
00:10:04,041 --> 00:10:05,750
There is no way I'll
allow you to go on a date

197
00:10:05,833 --> 00:10:08,041
dressed like some
dowdy transient bum.

198
00:10:08,125 --> 00:10:10,166
Ouch. Why so harsh?

199
00:10:10,250 --> 00:10:12,250
I do not dress like
a "transient bum"

200
00:10:12,333 --> 00:10:14,375
and you will take that back!

201
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,166
Got this!

202
00:10:24,916 --> 00:10:26,750
[CHIHO] There you are!

203
00:10:26,833 --> 00:10:27,625
Hey Chi.

204
00:10:27,708 --> 00:10:29,125
Oh wow, is that a new haircut?

205
00:10:29,208 --> 00:10:30,250
[CHIHO] Glad you noticed!

206
00:10:30,333 --> 00:10:32,125
Yeah. It's short.

207
00:10:32,208 --> 00:10:33,416
So what do you think?

208
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:35,041
[MAOU] Uh. Looks good.

209
00:10:35,125 --> 00:10:36,333
[CHIHO thinking] Score!

210
00:10:36,416 --> 00:10:37,875
[CHIHO] I like your outfit.

211
00:10:37,958 --> 00:10:40,125
I don't think I've ever seen
you all cleaned up like this.

212
00:10:40,208 --> 00:10:41,375
Huh?

213
00:10:41,458 --> 00:10:42,458
[CHIHO] Uh, not to say
you looked bad before;

214
00:10:42,541 --> 00:10:43,791
you always look good.

215
00:10:43,875 --> 00:10:45,583
It's just now you
look better is all.

216
00:10:45,666 --> 00:10:47,625
Um, I didn't mean better.

217
00:10:47,708 --> 00:10:50,500
What I mean is--
You look so cool.

218
00:10:50,583 --> 00:10:51,708
Yeah, my roommate
told me I needed

219
00:10:51,791 --> 00:10:53,583
to dress a little
nicer for our date.

220
00:10:53,666 --> 00:10:56,500
Wow. So are you saying you
think of this as a date?

221
00:10:56,583 --> 00:10:58,625
[MAOU] Uh. I guess so. Yeah.

222
00:10:58,708 --> 00:10:59,666
[CHIHO thinking] Score!

223
00:10:59,750 --> 00:11:01,083
[MAOU] So, what now?

224
00:11:01,166 --> 00:11:03,250
[CHIHO] There's a great café
not too far from here.

225
00:11:03,333 --> 00:11:05,708
It's cheap and
pretty laid back, too.

226
00:11:05,791 --> 00:11:07,125
[CHIHO] You'll love it!

227
00:11:07,208 --> 00:11:09,541
And since you're giving me
advice, it'll be my treat!

228
00:11:09,625 --> 00:11:10,958
Does that sound
like a good plan?

229
00:11:11,041 --> 00:11:12,541
I can't let you do that.

230
00:11:12,625 --> 00:11:15,416
I mean, thank you.
But I can't accept.

231
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:17,583
This lunch is on me.

232
00:11:17,666 --> 00:11:19,208
[CHIHO] Uh, Mister Maou!

233
00:11:19,291 --> 00:11:20,416
Hm?

234
00:11:20,500 --> 00:11:22,333
You see. The thing is--

235
00:11:22,416 --> 00:11:24,041
What's up?
Are you all right?

236
00:11:24,125 --> 00:11:27,083
Yeah. I just wanted
to hold your hand.

237
00:11:27,166 --> 00:11:30,000
[MAOU] Oh that's all?
Yeah, no problem.

238
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:34,291
You okay?

239
00:11:34,375 --> 00:11:36,166
Huh? Yeah, I'm great.

240
00:11:36,250 --> 00:11:39,291
Never better actually!
Thank you for asking, though.

241
00:11:39,375 --> 00:11:40,750
[MAOU] This way, making
our way through the crowd,

242
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:42,666
we won't get separated.

243
00:11:42,750 --> 00:11:44,125
You're right, that's true.

244
00:11:44,208 --> 00:11:46,458
Better safe than
sorry, I suppose.

245
00:11:56,125 --> 00:11:57,875
What sort of
"no good" are you up to?

246
00:11:57,958 --> 00:12:00,833
Ahh! Eh... Em... Em... Eh...
