of a "you know what"
as ever, then yes.

274
00:12:53,375 --> 00:12:57,041
But what I don't understand is
why they need to go on a date.

275
00:12:57,125 --> 00:12:58,708
[ASHIYA] I wondered
the same thing initially.

276
00:12:58,791 --> 00:13:01,208
But it's clear to me,
after observing her,

277
00:13:01,291 --> 00:13:02,458
that this "Sasaki" girl is more

278
00:13:02,541 --> 00:13:04,708
than just a little
fond of your old rival.

279
00:13:04,791 --> 00:13:06,000
[EMI] It seems so.

280
00:13:06,083 --> 00:13:08,666
Um. I'm sorry, that
doesn't bother you at all?

281
00:13:08,750 --> 00:13:10,000
[EMI] You want it to?

282
00:13:10,083 --> 00:13:13,000
Well-- No, I--I just
find it extremely unbearable

283
00:13:13,083 --> 00:13:15,250
and highly insolent that
a mere human girl has

284
00:13:15,333 --> 00:13:17,541
